Reasoning tasks in belief revision and logic-based abduction are typically studied in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with complexity theory, specifically the complexity of decision problems, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The CardMinSat problem is a decision problem, and thus the paper may also be relevant to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves propositional formulas and clauses, which are commonly used in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the satisfiability problem, which is a classic problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
